Class YanceesConnector

java.lang.Object
  edu.uci.isr.impromptu.common.YanceesConnector
All Implemented Interfaces:
edu.uci.isr.yancees.SubscriberInterface
public class YanceesConnector
extends java.lang.Object
implements edu.uci.isr.yancees.SubscriberInterface

Yancees connector to send and receive events. This is the Yancess interface between the peer owners (repository or pie) and the Yancees middleware. The peer manager discovers present peers, and uses this class to interact with Yancees. This class forwards the available peers to the service. TODO: architecture: make this ArchStudio compatible and delivery independent

peerJoin

public void peerJoin(java.lang.String peerName,
                     java.lang.String peerAddress)
Tell the service that a new peer has joined. Yancees maintains a different set of peers than the proxyFilter or the pie for a separate configuration. Yancees needs to deliver to every one, but the repository signifies the presense of a peer. Still, this is somewhat artificial.

Parameters:
peerName - the name of the newly joined peer
peerAddress - the address of the newly joined peer
